%2Fdonald-trump-supreme-court-nominations%2F%5C%22%3Eshould%20align%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20his%20own.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20his%20Jan.%206%2C%202021%2C%20speech%20before%20the%20attack%20on%20the%20U.S.%20Capitol%2C%20Trump%20sounded%20miffed%20at%20the%20three%20justices%20he%20had%20nominated%20to%20the%20Supreme%20Court.%20They%20were%20ruling%20against%20him%20now%2C%20he%20said%2C%20perhaps%20to%20counter%20the%20perception%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2023%2F12%2F21%2Fus%2Fpolitics%2Ftrump-supreme-court.html%5C%22%3E%E2%80%9Cthey%E2%80%99re%20my%20puppets.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EModern%20presidents%20have%20always%20sought%20to%20mould%20the%20judiciary%20by%20selecting%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.upress.virginia.edu%2Ftitle%2F3596%2F%5C%22%3Ejustices%20whose%20records%3C%2Fa%3E%20align%20with%20the%20nominating%20president%E2%80%99s%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fyalebooks.yale.edu%2Fbook%2F9780300080735%2Fpicking-federal-judges%2F%5C%22%3Epolitical%20preferences%3C%2Fa%3E.%20But%20historically%2C%20presidents%20were%20careful%20to%20discuss%20the%20courts%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cambridge.org%2Fcore%2Fbooks%2Fcurbing-the-court%2F97B607067A2E7392C2223EF7E642FC7A%5C%22%3Elegalistic%20terms%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdoi.org%2F10.1111%2F1468-2508.00207%5C%22%3Eavoid%20politicizing%20the%20judiciary%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETrump%20flouted%20those%20norms.%20In%20an%20unusual%20move%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2016%2F05%2F19%2Fus%2Fpolitics%2Fdonald-trump-supreme-court-nominees.html%5C%22%3Ehe%20released%20a%20list%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20potential%20Supreme%20Court%20nominees%20while%20campaigning%20for%20the%202016%20GOP%20presidential%20nomination%2C%20touting%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftime.com%2F4266700%2Fdonald-trump-supreme-court-nominations%2F%5C%22%3Econservative%20credentials%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20the%20nam