tution%20%E2%80%93%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20depends%20on%20other%20institutions%20for%20enforcement%20of%20its%20opinions.%20The%20court%20lacks%20the%20literal%20force%20or%20money%20to%20enforce%20its%20decisions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EConsider%20the%20Supreme%20Court%E2%80%99s%20famous%201954%20ruling%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.oyez.org%2Fcases%2F1940-1955%2F347us483%5C%22%3EBrown%20v.%20Board%20of%20Education%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20ordered%20the%20end%20of%20school%20segregation.%20That%20ruling%20did%20not%20get%20enforced%20in%20most%20of%20the%20South%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdoi.org%2F10.1111%2Fajps.12069%5C%22%3Euntil%20the%20president%20and%20Congress%20passed%20laws%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20punished%20schools%20that%20refused%20to%20integrate.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThose%20institutions%20enforce%20Supreme%20Court%20decisions%20only%20because%20the%20public%20believes%20the%20court%20is%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdoi.org%2F10.1111%2F1540-5907.00025%5C%22%3Elegitimate%20legal%20institution%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20the%20authority%20to%20make%20decisions%20about%20the%20law%20and%20get%20them%20enforced.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20belief%20in%20judicial%20authority%20stems%20from%20several%20different%20sources%2C%20including%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.degruyter.com%2Fdocument%2Fdoi%2F10.1515%2F9781400830602%2Fhtml%5C%22%3Eelementary%20education%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20democratic%20values%2C%20the%20justices%E2%80%99%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpress.umich.edu%2FBooks%2FT%2FThe-Limits-of-Legitimacy2%5C%22%3Econcerted%20efforts%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdoi.org%2F10.1177%2F1065912918801563%5C%22%3Eto%20avoid%3C%2Fa%3E%20all%20but%20the%20most%20favorable%20media%20attention%2C%20their%20focus%20on%20showing%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdoi.org%2F10.1111%2Fj.1540-5907.2012.00616.x%5C%22%3Ethe%20principled%20nature%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20their%20decision-making%20process%2C%20their%20aim%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdoi.org%2F10.1017%2Fjlc.2023.15%5C%22%3Emitigate%20negative%20public%20sentiment%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20even%20their%20decision%20to%20separate%20themselves%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdoi.org%2F10.1111%2Flasr.12104%5C%22%3Ewearing%20robes%20to%20political%20events%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETo%20be%20sure%2C%20people%20are%20not%20naive%20about%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdoi.org%2F10.1146%2Fannurev-polisci-032211-214229%5C%22%3Epolitical%20nature%20of%20Supreme%20Court%20decision-making%3C%2Fa%3E.%20But%20as%20long%20as%20the%20justices%E2%80%99%20decision-making%20appears%20principled%2C%20research%20has%20found%20that%20the%20court%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdoi.org%2F10.1111%2Fj.1540-5893.2011.00432.x%5C%22%3Eremains%20legitimate%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20the%20public%2C%20even%20if%20the%20court%20issues%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdoi.org%2F10.1146%2Fannurev-lawsocsci-110413-030546%5C%22%3Edecision%20the%20public%20dislikes%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETypically%2C%20the%20justices%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpress.princeton.edu%2Fbooks%2Fpaperback%2F9780691136332%2Fthe-politics-of-precedent-on-the-us-supreme-court%5C%22%3Elean%20on%20precedent%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20defend%20their%20rulings%2C%20but%20the%20justices%20cannot%20do%20so%20in%20the%20Trump%20Colorado%20ballot%20case.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthehill.com%2Fopinion%2Fjudiciary%2F4435677-the-supreme-court-cant-punt-on-trumps-disqualification-without-threatening-the-constitution%2F%5C%22%3ENo%20precedent%20exists%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECombined%20with%20the%20court%E2%80%99s%20low%20popular%20support%2C%20moving%20into%20uncharted%20legal%20territory%20means%20the%20justices%20face%2C%20for%20the%20first%20time%20in%20a%20while%2C%20the%20possibility%20that%20people%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.npr.org%2F2023%2F09%2F26%2F1200906844%2Fsupreme-court-alabama-voting-case%5C%22%3Emight%20defy%3C%2Fa%3E%20or%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.pbs.org%2Fnewshour%2Fshow%2Fborder-standoff-between-texas-feds-intensifies-as-governor-defies-supreme-court-ruling%5C%22%3Eignore%20their%20rulings%3C%2Fa%3E.%20In%20fact%2C%20Sen.%20J.D.%20Vance%2C%20a%20Republican%20from%20Ohio%2C%20suggested%20in%20a%20recent%20interview%20that%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.foxnews.com%2Fvideo%2F6346242779112%5C%22%3Epresident%20could%20defy%20the%20Supreme%20Court%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EConsequently%2C%20while%20the%20justices%E2%80%99%20decision%20will%20be%20important%20for%20constitutional%20and%20democratic%20reasons%2C%20the%20public%E2%80%99s%20response%20to%20the%20ruling%20will%20be%20just%20as%20important%20for%20democracy%20and%20the%20rule%20of%20law%20in%20the%20U.S.%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20Conversation%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcounter.theconversation.com%2Fcontent%2F222354%2Fcount.gif%3Fdistributor%3Drepublish-lightbox-basic%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%2Fprofiles%2Fjessica-a-schoenherr-1507683%5C%22%3EJessica%20A.%20Schoenherr%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Assistant%20Professor%20of%20Political%20Science%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%2Finstitutions%2Funiversity-of-south-carolina-1755%5C%22%3EUniversity%20of%20South%20Carolina%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%2Fprofiles%2Fjonathan-m-king-1507686%5C%22%3EJonathan%20M.%20King%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Assistant%20Professor%20of%20Political%20Science%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%2Finstitutions%2Fwest-virginia-university-1375%5C%22%3EWest%20Virginia%20University%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20article%20is%20republished%20from%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%5C%22%3EThe%20Conversation%3C%2Fa%3E%20under%20a%20Creative%20Commons%20license.%20Read%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3